   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This program promotes SPM in Latin America through national and regional microfinance networks. Social Performance Management (SPM) uses an array of best practices to help microfinance providers set clear social objectives, monitor and assess progress, and use results to design operations that balance social benefits and institutional financial sustainability. Based on learnings in Latin America, SPM will be promoted throughout Africa, starting with a pilot in Senegal.</narrative>
